Chinese state - run news agency Xinhua reported that at least seven persons have been killed and 22 others injured in Tibet in the quake which has caused landslides and has disrupted traffic , power and water supplies as well as telecommunication in Yadong County , an area 40 km away from Sikkim . Three people were killed at Lainchaur in Kathmandu , two in Sunsari district , and one each in Dhankuta and Sankhuwasabha districts in eastern Nepal , according to home ministry sources in the Nepalese capital .